Rating: 3
Very good. Nice flavors and you could use any mild, flaky white fish. We all enjoyed it and the presentation will impress your guests.

Rating: 3
Great recipe and a wonderful presentation when the fish, leeks and potatoes are stacked. Suggestions: I intensified the flavor by "enhancing" the mustard with a tsp of fresh rosemary, a pinch of salt, a couple of twists of fresh ground black pepper and a qurter tsp of sugar (cuts the acidity and enhances the flavor without noticeable sweetness). Also, I used dry vermouth instead of chicken stock to make a totally meatless dish and the flavor was terrific (thought of using fish stock but decided it might fight with the flavor of the bass). The vinaigrette was wonderful, but be sure to use "real" balsalmico di modena and not the supermarket stuff. jk new york

